src: Die Audio-Qualität von Vorbis misst man besser nicht in kilobit pro Sekunde, sondern auf einer Qualitätsskala von -1 bis 10. Qualität -1 entspricht ungefähr 45 KBit/Sek., 5 ist ungefähr 160 KBit/Sek. und 10 ergibt in etwa 400 KBit/Sekunde. CD-nahe Qualität wird ungefähr bei Stufe 5 erreicht, verlustlose Stereo-Komprimierung erreicht man ca. bei Stufe 6. Die Voreinstellung ist 3, damit erreicht man etwa 110 KBit/Sek. und wesentlich kleinere Dateien bei besserer Qualität als .mp3 mit 128 KBit/Sek. Diese Erklärung wurde aus der FAQ von www.vorbis.com kopiert.
ref: Vorbis' audio quality is not best measured in kilobits per second, but on a scale from -1 to 10 called "quality". For now, quality -1 is roughly equivalent to 45kbps average, 5 is roughly 160kbps, and 10 gives about 400kbps. Most people seeking very-near-CD-quality audio encode at a quality of 5 or, for lossless stereo coupling, 6. The default setting is quality 3, which at approximately 110kbps gives a smaller filesize and significantly better fidelity than. mp3 compression at 128kbps. This explanation was copied from the www. vorbis. com FAQ.
draft: The audio quality of Vorbis should not be measured in kilobits per second, but rather on a quality scale from -1 to 10. Quality -1 is approximately 45 Kbps, 5 is approximately 160 Kbps, and 10 is around 400 Kbps. CD-quality is reached at level 5, while lossless stereo compression is achieved around level 6. The default setting is 3, which yields approximately 110 Kbps and significantly smaller files with better quality than .mp3 at 128 Kbps. This explanation was copied from the FAQ of www.vorbis.com.
hil: The audio quality of Vorbis is best measured not in kilobits per second, but on a quality scale from -1 to 10. Quality -1 is approximately 45 Kbps, 5 is approximately 160 Kbps, and 10 is around 400 Kbps. CD-quality is achieved at level 5, while lossless stereo compression is achieved at around level 6. The default setting is 3, which yields approximately 110 Kbps and significantly smaller files with better quality than .mp3 at 128 Kbps. This explanation was copied from the FAQ of www.vorbis.com.
compare: The audio quality of Vorbis should not be measured in kilobits per second, but rather on a quality scale from -1 to 10. Quality -1 is approximately 45 Kbps, 5 is approximately 160 Kbps, and 10 is around 400 Kbps. CD-quality is reached at level 5, while lossless stereo compression is achieved around level 6. The default setting is 3, which yields approximately 110 Kbps and significantly smaller files with better quality than .mp3 at 128 Kbps. This explanation was copied from the FAQ of www.vorbis.com.

hil: When editing an image, the technique called 'unsharp mask' is often used to sharpen areas that should appear sharp. The unsharp mask makes edges appear sharper by enhancing the contrast along the edge. This is done by first creating a blurred copy of the image, then subtracting the blurred copy from the original to create an image mask. The image mask is then added back to the original image using a specified strength and threshold.

Hopefully, this situation will change in the future; for now, you'll need some basic knowledge of how an & XML; document works (or & HTML;, which is a subset of & XML;). [The action concept needs to be discussed in more detail -- kt.]
draft: With the help of the actions concept from & Qt; and & kde;, you can change the menu bar and toolbars of & koffice; arbitrarily. Unfortunately, there are no easy-to-use dialogs for this so far. hil: Using the actions concept from & Qt; and & kde;, you can customize the menu bar and toolbars of & koffice; as much as you like. Der unterste linke Knopf schaltet die zufällige Wiedergabe der Stücke auf der & CD; ein, während der rechte die Dauerwiederholung schaltet, so dass die & CD; nach dem letzten Titel wieder von vorne startet.
ref: The uppermost button in the above diagram toggles between playing and pausing the & CD;. The left button in the second row stops playing the & CD;. The right button in the second row ejects the & CD;. The two buttons in the third row skip forward (right) or backward (left) to the beginning of the next or previous track. The left button in the bottom row toggles random play order on and off; the right button in the bottom row toggles looping, so that the & CD; will start playing again from the beginning when the end of the last audio track is reached.
draft: The top button in the illustration above starts or pauses playback. The left button in the second row stops the playback of the CD, while the one to the right ejects the CD. The buttons in the third row jump to the beginning of the previous and next tracks. The bottom left button turns on random playback of the tracks on the CD, while the right button switches to repeat mode, so the CD starts again from the beginning after the last track.
hil: The top button in the illustration above starts or stops playback. The left button in the second row stops playback of the CD, while the one to the right ejects the CD. The buttons in the third row jump to the beginning of the previous and next tracks. The bottom left button turns on random playback of the tracks on the CD, while the right button switches to repeat mode, so the CD starts again from the beginning after the last track.
compare: The top button in the illustration above starts or pauses playback. The left button in the second row stops the playback of the CD, while the one to the right ejects the CD. The buttons in the third row jump to the beginning of the previous and next tracks. The bottom left button turns on random playback of the tracks on the CD, while the right button switches to repeat mode, so the CD starts again from the beginning after the last track.

src: Ein Feind wird„ ausgetrickst“, indem ein Loch gegraben und über den Kopf des hineingefallenen Feindes hinweg gelaufen wird. Gleichzeitig wird ihm dabei alles von ihm getragene Gold abgenommen. src: Ein Kredit ist eine Vereinbarung bei der ein Kreditnehmer von einem Kreditgeber Geld erhält und sich bereiterklärt, das Geld zu einem späteren Zeitpunkt zurückzuzahlen. & kappname; erlaubt es Ihnen, Kredite zu verfolgen, bei denen Sie selbst der Kreditgeber sind und Geld verliehen haben, oder Sie als Kreditnehmer einen Kredit aufgenommen haben. Die meisten Privatpersonen nehmen Kredite auf, als dass sie Geld verleihen, so dass Sie i.d.R. der Kreditnehmer und ein Geldinstitut der Kreditgeber sind. Wenn Sie Geld an ein Familienmitglied oder einen Freund verleihen können Sie natürlich & kappname; dazu verwenden, auch diesen Kredit zu überwachen.
ref: A loan is an agreement under which a borrower receives money from a lender and agrees to repay the money at some future date. & kappname; allows you to track loans by which you, as borrower, borrow money from or, as lender, lend money to someone else. Most individuals borrow more than they lend, so you will generally be the borrower and a finance company will generally be the lender. If you lend money to a family member or a friend, you can use & kappname; to keep track of this loan as well.
draft: A loan is an agreement in which a borrower receives money from a lender and agrees to pay back the money at a later time. & kappname; allows you to track loans where you are the lender and have lent money or where you have taken out a loan as the borrower. Most individuals take out loans rather than lending money, so you are usually the borrower and a financial institution is the lender. If you lend money to a family member or friend, you can of course use & kappname; to track this loan as well.
hil: A loan is an agreement in which a borrower receives money from a lender and agrees to pay back the money at a later time. & kappname; allows you to track loans where you are the lender and have lent money or where you have taken out a loan as the borrower. Most individuals take out loans rather than lending money, so you are usually the borrower and a financial institution is the lender. If you lend money to a family member or friend, you can of course use & kappname; to track this loan as well.

src: Normalerweise bekommen Sie neue Zertifikate durch Überprüfen von Signaturen in E-Mail-Nachrichten, weil die Zertifikate normalerweise in die Signaturen, die damit vorgenommen wurden, eingebettet werden. Wenn Sie aber jemandem eine Nachricht senden wollen, mit dem Sie bisher noch keinen Kontakt hatten, dann müssen Sie das Zertifikat aus einem LDAP-Ordner (gpgsm; kann das aber auch automatisch für Sie tun) oder einer Datei holen. Außerdem müssen Sie Ihr eigenes Zertifikat importieren, nachdem Sie die Antwort der & ca; auf Ihre Zertifizierungsanfrage bekommen haben.
ref: Most of the time, you will acquire new certificates by verifying signatures in emails, since certificates are embedded in the signatures made using them most of the time. However, if you need to send a mail to someone you have not yet had contact with, you need to fetch the certificate from an LDAP folder (although & gpgsm; can do this automatically), or from a file. You also need to import your own certificate after receiving the & ca; answer to your certification request.
draft: Normally you receive new certificates by verifying signatures in email messages because the certificates are usually embedded in the signatures made with them. However, if you want to send a message to someone with whom you have not yet had any contact, you must retrieve the certificate from an LDAP directory (gpgsm can also do this automatically for you) or a file. In addition, you must import your own certificate after receiving the response from the & ca; to your certification request.
hil: Normally, you obtain new certificates by verifying signatures in email messages because the certificates are usually embedded in the signatures made with them. However, if you want to send a message to someone with whom you have not yet had any contact, you must retrieve the certificate from an LDAP directory (gpgsm can also do this automatically for you) or a file. In addition, you must import your own certificate after receiving the response from the CA to your certification request.
compare: Normally, you obtain new certificates by verifying signatures in email messages because the certificates are usually embedded in the signatures made with them. However, if you want to send a message to someone with whom you have not yet had any contact, you must retrieve the certificate from an LDAP directory (gpgsm can also do this automatically for you) or a file. In addition, you must import your own certificate after receiving the response from the CA to your certification request.

In einigen Fällen ist es sinnvoll die Helligkeit gleichzeitig zu justieren. Die Helligkeit hier ist ähnlich zu der Leuchtstärke aus dem Werkzeug Leuchstärke/Kontrast/Gamma. Sie werden allerdings durch unterschiedliche Kombinationen der Rot-, Grün- und Blaukanäle erzeugt.
ref: If your image is washed out (which can easily happen when you take images in bright light) try the Hue/ Saturation/ Lightness tool, which gives you three sliders to manipulate, for Hue, Saturation, and Lightness. draft: If your image looks faded. This can easily happen, for example, if you take photos in bright sunshine, you should try the color shading/saturation/brightness tool. In some cases, it makes sense to adjust the brightness at the same time. The brightness here is similar to the luminance from the luminance/contrast/gamma tool. However, they are generated by different combinations of the red, green and blue channels.
hil: If your image looks faded, for example, when taking photos in bright sunshine, you should try the color shading/saturation/brightness tool. compare: If your image looks faded. This can easily happen, for example, if you take photos in bright sunshine, you should try the color shading/saturation/brightness tool. src: Was versteht man unter Instant Messaging (im;)? Bei & im; handelt es sich um eine Form der Kommunikation mit Freunden über das Internet. Das klingt ähnlich wie E-Mail, allerdings kann selbst eine kurze Konversation per E-Mail schon anstrengend sein. Sie müssen jedes Mal auf Antworten klicken, dann die richtige Stelle im Text finden und schließlich die E-Mail absenden. Es vergeht immer eine gewisse Wartezeit, bis die nächste Nachricht ankommt. Mit & im; ist die Konversation ähnlich flüssig wie per Telefon oder im persönlichen Gespräch. Die Nachrichten werden in ein gemeinsames Fenster eingegeben.
ref: What is Instant Messaging (im;)? & im; is a way for you to communicate instantly with your friends over the Internet. That might not sound so different to email. Have you ever noticed how cumbersome it is to have a brief conversation via email? You have to click Reply to each message, then find the right spot in the message to type something new, then send it. Then you have to wait for the next message to arrive! & im; lets you to have a conversation almost as naturally as on the phone or face to face, by typing messages into a window shared between you and your friend's screens.
draft: What is meant by Instant Messaging (IM)? With IM, it is a form of communication with friends over the internet. This sounds similar to email, but even a short conversation via email can be exhausting. You have to click on replies every time, then find the right place in the text and finally send the email. There is always a certain waiting time until the next message arrives. With IM, the conversation is as fluid as talking on the phone or in person. The messages are entered into a shared window.
hil: Instant Messaging (IM) is a form of communication with friends over the internet. It is similar to email, but even a short conversation via email can be exhausting. You have to click on replies every time, then find the right place in the text and finally send the email. There is always a certain waiting time until the next message arrives. With IM, the conversation is as fluid as talking on the phone or in person, as the messages are entered into a shared window.
compare: What is meant by Instant Messaging (IM)? With IM, it is a form of communication with friends over the internet. This sounds similar to email, but even a short conversation via email can be exhausting. You have to click on replies every time, then find the right place in the text and finally send the email. There is always a certain waiting time until the next message arrives. With IM, the conversation is as fluid as talking on the phone or in person. The messages are entered into a shared window.

src: Fundamentstapel werden von der Basiskarte aufsteigend nach Farbe aufgebaut. Neue Fundamentstapel werden begonnen, wenn eine Karte des gleichen Ranges wie die Basiskarte auf leere Fundamentstapel gelegt wird. Asse werden auf Könige und Zweien auf Asse abgelegt. Die Karten in den Fundamentstapeln sind noch im Spiel. Durch einen Doppelklick auf eine Karte wird diese auf den entsprechenden Fundamentstapel gelegt, falls solch ein Zug möglich ist.
ref: Foundations are built up in suit from the base card. New Foundations are started when a card of the same rank as the base card is placed on empty Foundation piles. Aces are placed on Kings, and twos on Aces. Cards in Foundations are still in play. Double clicking on a card will move it to the appropriate Foundation pile if such a move is possible.
draft: Foundation piles are built up from the base card in ascending order by color. New foundation piles are started when a card of the same rank as the base card is placed on empty foundation piles. Aces are placed on kings and twos are placed on aces. The cards in the foundation piles are still in the game. A double-click on a card places it on the corresponding foundation pile if such a move is possible.
hil: Foundation piles are built up by suit from the base card in ascending order. New foundations are started when a card of the same rank as the base card is placed on empty foundations. Aces are placed on kings and twos are placed on aces. The cards in the foundation piles are still in the game. Double-clicking a card places it on the corresponding foundation pile if such a move is possible.
compare: Foundation piles are built up from the base card in ascending order by color. New foundation piles are started when a card of the same rank as the base card is placed on empty foundation piles. Aces are placed on kings and twos are placed on aces. The cards in the foundation piles are still in the game. A double-click on a card places it on the corresponding foundation pile if such a move is possible.
